武汉“封城”后，25岁的中学老师吴悠，骑上电瓶车为网上求助者义务送药。
Wuhan "closed the city," 25-year-old secondary school teacher Wu Yu, riding a battery car for online clients to volunteer medicine.
截至目前，他和朋友们已经为600多户求助者送去药品和防护物资。
So far, he and his friends have sent medicines and protective materials to more than 600 families.
吴悠每天十点出门，电瓶车一次充满电只能骑行30公里，有些求助者居住的地方比较远，车子的电常常不够用，吴悠就找公共厕所为车子充电。
Wu Yo goes out at 10: 00 every day, the electric car is full of electricity can only ride 30 kilometers, some suitors live far away, the car is often not enough electricity, Wu Yo found public toilets to recharge the car.
刚开始，所有药品和防护物资吴悠一律免费赠送，但出现了哄抢、囤药的现象。
At the beginning, all drugs and protective materials Wu Yili free of charge, but there was looting, hoarding of drugs.
为了将药品精准给予需急救的病人手中，吴悠和四川志愿者协商后，决定将奥司他韦、阿比多尔、莫西沙星和硫酸羟氯喹片，以低于工厂价的价格出售。
In order to give the drugs precisely to patients in need of emergency treatment, Wu and volunteers in Sichuan decided to sell oseltamivir, Abidor, moxifloxacin sulphate and hydroxychloroquine sulphate at a price lower than the factory price.
出售所得返还给捐赠方，用来继续购买药品。
Proceeds from the sale are returned to donors for continued purchase of medicines.
连花清瘟、口罩、酒精等防护物资，仍旧无偿赠送。
Even Huaqing Rinderpest, masks, alcohol and other protective materials, still free of charge.
近日，有人以非法售药和牟利举报了吴悠。
Recently, someone reported Wu Yo for selling illegal drugs and making profits.
在配合调查时，吴悠奶奶因脑溢血昏迷，被送进医院。
In cooperation with the investigation, Grandma Wu Yu was hospitalized for a cerebral haemorrhage.
“当时义务送药就是希望能推动疫情早日结束，这样奶奶就能早点住进医院，不会患上老年痴呆，不会忘记我。
"The idea was to give the medicine so that it could end as soon as possible so that Grandma could be admitted to the hospital earlier and not suffer from Alzheimer's disease and not forget me.
”以下是送药人吴悠的完整版视频。
Here is a full-length video of the drug delivery person.
